%% Diagram: HMAC-SHA256 signing + edge verification flow
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Caller App
    participant Signer as Signature Service
    participant Edge as CDN / Edge Worker
    participant Origin

    Note over App,Signer: 1. Mint signed URL
    App->>Signer: path, exp, kid, tenantId
    Signer->>Signer: canonical = METHOD + path + exp + host + tenantId
    Signer->>Signer: sig = base64url(HMAC-SHA256(secret_kid, canonical))
    Signer-->>App: URL?sig=...&exp=...&kid=...

    Note over App,Edge: 2. Use signed URL
    App->>Edge: GET URL
    Edge->>Edge: parse sig, exp, kid
    Edge->>Edge: reject if now > exp
    Edge->>Edge: lookup secret_kid (KV / secret store)
    Edge->>Edge: recompute canonical + HMAC
    alt timingSafeEqual ok
        Edge->>Edge: strip sig/exp/kid from cache key
        Edge->>Origin: forward (normalized cache key)
        Origin-->>Edge: 200 image bytes
        Edge-->>App: 200 (cacheable)
    else mismatch or expired
        Edge-->>App: 401 Unauthorized
    end
